00:02:13.160 --> 00:02:15.470
It truly is an honor
to wake up each morning

00:02:15.470 --> 00:02:18.430
and read our mission statement
that says that we are trying

00:02:18.430 --> 00:02:19.730
to eradicate poverty

00:02:19.730 --> 00:02:23.420
by leveraging family
based education solutions.

00:02:23.420 --> 00:02:26.540
And our President and founder,
Sharon Darling, 30 years ago,

00:02:26.540 --> 00:02:29.960
discovered through her work as
an adult literacy instructor

00:02:29.960 --> 00:02:32.690
in Kentucky and in
specifically in Appalachian,

00:02:32.690 --> 00:02:36.650
Eastern Kentucky, that in order
to truly get at the root issues

00:02:36.650 --> 00:02:39.020
of helping families
climb out of poverty,

00:02:39.020 --> 00:02:41.460
we had to build both
adult literacy skills

00:02:41.460 --> 00:02:45.640
and child literacy skills, and
bring them together to learn.

00:02:45.640 --> 00:02:48.390
And luckily what she found out
through her own cardiac research

00:02:48.390 --> 00:02:51.360
or what she knew was right in
her heart has been confirmed

00:02:51.360 --> 00:02:54.480
through three decades of
research now that we can look to

00:02:54.480 --> 00:02:55.840
and performance that tells us

00:02:55.840 --> 00:02:58.950
that family literacy is truly
a way to make great gains

00:02:58.950 --> 00:03:00.700
for the families who
need it the most.

00:03:00.700 --> 00:03:02.410
This is what gets me
out of bed every morning

00:03:02.410 --> 00:03:06.140
and it really is the
root of developing

00:03:06.140 --> 00:03:08.750
and sustaining readers
across a lifespan.

00:03:08.750 --> 00:03:11.880
At NCFL, we know that
the genesis of reading

00:03:11.880 --> 00:03:15.560
and literacy happens the moment
that a child hears her mother

00:03:15.560 --> 00:03:18.370
or father or caregiver
say words to them.

00:03:18.370 --> 00:03:20.230
And hopefully that's
through reading.

00:03:20.230 --> 00:03:23.250
From there, we reinforce
those activities and we hope

00:03:23.250 --> 00:03:24.590
that by creating

00:03:24.590 --> 00:03:26.770
that intergenerational
reading experience,

00:03:26.770 --> 00:03:31.170
that we create lifelong learners
for all children and families.

00:03:31.170 --> 00:03:33.750
And here today, we've heard
many of the dire statistics

00:03:33.750 --> 00:03:37.370
about low literacy,
illiteracy, and the things

00:03:37.370 --> 00:03:40.470
that those horrible parts
of our society bring as far

00:03:40.470 --> 00:03:43.760
as putting barriers in place
for families to be successful.

00:03:43.760 --> 00:03:46.490
And that's something we're
very concerned about at NCFL

00:03:46.490 --> 00:03:49.000
but I didn't want to focus
more on the topic of reading

00:03:49.000 --> 00:03:51.760
which is one way we
practice literacy, of course.

00:03:51.760 --> 00:03:54.530
And we all know that reading
builds background knowledge

00:03:54.530 --> 00:03:57.500
and it helps us learn and we
can actually access society

00:03:57.500 --> 00:03:59.780
through the process
of reading but some

00:03:59.780 --> 00:04:01.730
of the other things I was
interested to find out --

00:04:01.730 --> 00:04:03.530
some of you probably know this.

00:04:03.530 --> 00:04:06.280
But reading regularly
can reduce stress.

00:04:06.280 --> 00:04:09.800
It can keep your brain
sharp until later adulthood.

00:04:09.800 --> 00:04:12.000
There are even a few studies
that say it may protect

00:04:12.000 --> 00:04:15.460
against dementia in older
adults by 3 to 7 years.

00:04:15.460 --> 00:04:17.350
Just reading throughout
a lifetime.

00:04:17.350 --> 00:04:19.640
You sleep better when
you read regularly.

00:04:19.640 --> 00:04:22.380
It increases empathy which
was mentioned before.

00:04:22.380 --> 00:04:24.460
And I think that's
something that's very serious

00:04:24.460 --> 00:04:25.760
at this point in our society.

00:04:25.760 --> 00:04:28.790
We could definitely benefit
from some more empathy.

00:04:28.790 --> 00:04:30.310
It can ease depression.

00:04:30.310 --> 00:04:32.040
And my personal favorite
that I found

00:04:32.040 --> 00:04:35.650
in my quick research was it can
actually cultivate your ability

00:04:35.650 --> 00:04:37.800
to read minds.

00:04:37.800 --> 00:04:39.920
[Laughter] So just
imagine what a group

00:04:39.920 --> 00:04:42.870
of literacy professionals
can do when we learn how

00:04:42.870 --> 00:04:45.480
to read minds better and
get people to do what it is

00:04:45.480 --> 00:04:47.760
that we want them to do.

