00:24:47.580 --> 00:24:51.620
Along the way, we've been able
to donate 25 million books

00:24:51.620 --> 00:24:53.690
to countries all over the world,

00:24:53.690 --> 00:24:55.840
organizations all
over the world.

00:24:55.840 --> 00:24:57.720
Some of you in this room
have been recipients

00:24:57.720 --> 00:25:02.340
of either book donations
or monetary donations.

00:25:02.340 --> 00:25:05.900
We just recently hit the
$27 million mark in terms

00:25:05.900 --> 00:25:09.530
of money that's been donated
to literacy organizations

00:25:09.530 --> 00:25:11.510
or libraries around the world.

00:25:11.510 --> 00:25:14.680
So we're really proud of what
we do at Better World Books.

00:25:14.680 --> 00:25:20.060
Our 500 employees are spread out
in four distribution centers.

00:25:20.060 --> 00:25:24.890
We work with approximately 4,000
libraries in North America.

00:25:24.890 --> 00:25:29.790
Globally we have 8,000 book
suppliers that send books to us.

00:25:29.790 --> 00:25:34.450
And we're taking those books
and either reselling them online

00:25:34.450 --> 00:25:36.930
on one of the 30
different marketplaces

00:25:36.930 --> 00:25:38.540
that we sell through.

00:25:38.540 --> 00:25:41.230
Anytime we sell a book
on BetterWorldBooks.com,

00:25:41.230 --> 00:25:42.780
we're donating a book.

00:25:42.780 --> 00:25:44.510
So it's kind of like
Tom's Shoes.

00:25:44.510 --> 00:25:47.600
It's a book for book program.

00:25:47.600 --> 00:25:51.980
And if we can't donate the book,
we're going to keep the book

00:25:51.980 --> 00:25:54.580
out of the landfill
and recycle it.

00:25:54.580 --> 00:25:56.870
So at any given point,
